<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1800] Documentation text not always escaped correctly when rendered to HTML</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1800</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Comments containing non-ascii characters (like for example the swedish &quot;Vi m&#228;ter temperaturer i &#176;C&quot;) show up incorrectly in the generated HTML file. Only a handful of characters is encoded at all, and only at a few rare occasions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
