                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13538460" author="jensg" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2012 22:04:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The careful observer will notice that I didn&apos;t use the escape_[] table by intention. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13538518" author="carlyeks" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2012 23:10:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you change test/DocTest.thrift to demonstrate the change that you made? I&apos;m not able to get it to properly escape the characters (instead, it is adding additional bogus characters).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13539007" author="jensg" created="Sun, 23 Dec 2012 09:55:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Occurs on probably all platforms, when IDL is plain text. However it works when the Input is already UTF-8 w/o BOM. I am going to revise my patch to work in both cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13539082" author="jensg" created="Sun, 23 Dec 2012 20:04:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Revised patch, now handles both cases. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13539098" author="carlyeks" created="Sun, 23 Dec 2012 21:39:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LGTM&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
